  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study to ascertain the number of children with moyamoya in the UK, their presenting
      features, clinical course and outcomes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study ahs 3 components:

        1. Patient identification via the British Paediatric Surveillance Unit, and the 21
           collaborating centres

        2. Record review/patient interview to determine clinical features &amp; outcomes

        3. Centralised review of imaging data to ascertain radiological phenotypes
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
